Does economic development depend on a class of super-wealthy tycoons? And is that such a bad thing?

In her book Rich People, Poor Countries, economist Caroline Freund says yes and no. As a former World Bank official in the Middle East, she saw countries wracked by crony capitalism—but also knew that some countries had succeeded in sharing prosperity alongside a class of new billionaires.
